rComments: So he's hard to understand and his writing is VERY messy. He would stand in front of the board after writing on it so you can't copy anything down, and when he finally moves he erases it. Every. single. person in my class had no idea what was going on, we were winging it. He is a very easy grader and nice, but he is a bad teacher. I learned nothing

Lectures are confusing and boring. He struggles to get certain points across, meaning you have to really read into the PP (which themselves can sometimes be hard to understand). His accent at first is a little hard to understand. Really great guy, cares about students and tries to interact with them. Always takes time to answer questions, email him

His lectures were the most boring, tedious lectures I have ever sat through. He is a nice guy who means well, but his teaching could use a lot of work. He doesn't effectively communicate the material. Make sure you have the textbook, all of the assignments are questions from the textbook. He is a VERY easy grader, but you'll need to teach yourself.
New prof but overall really nice guy who cares about his students and listening to student evaluations to improve as a prof. The exams are extremely fair and office hours really help!
